First-line treatment regimens are the preferred recommendation of local guideline authors.
Second-line regimens should be considered for patients:
recently exposed to first-line antibiotics;
failing first-line antibiotics;
according to relevant culture and susceptibility results;
or with contra-indication to first-line antibiotics.

First-line treatment regimens are the preferred recommendation of local guideline authors.
Second-line regimens should be considered for patients:
with previous or current Pseudomonas;
recently exposed to first-line antibiotics;
failing first-line antibiotics;
according to relevant culture and susceptibility results;
or with contra-indication to first-line antibiotics.
